Highest Cost Orders

Find the customer with the highest total order cost between 2019-02-01 to 2019-05-01. Output their first name, total cost of their items, and the date.

For simplicity, you can assume that every first name in the dataset is unique.

customers

id  int
first_name  varchar
last_name varchar
city  varchar
address varchar
phone_number  varchar

orders

id  int
cust_id int
order_date  datetime
order_quantity  int
order_details varchar
order_cost  int



select a.first_name,order_date,sum(order_cost*order_quantity) as total_order_amt
from customers a,
orders b
where a.id=b.cust_id and
order_date between '2019-02-01' and '2019-05-01'
group by first_name,order_date
HAVING sum(order_cost*order_quantity) >= (select sum(order_cost*order_quantity) 
                                          from orders 
                                          group by cust_id, order_date 
                                          order by sum(order_cost*order_quantity) desc 
                                          limit 1)
;
